counterharm_basic:
Mi deh reason seh `return_data` a one dictionary fi true. So far, no key name 'fpath' (weh a 'sig9') deh inna it yet, so dat a mek di error pop up. 

Fi fix dis, yuh can set up `rslt` as a defaultdict weh hold list dem. Dis way, every key go get im own empty list when yuh first touch it. Check how yuh can tweak di code yah: 

```python
from collections import defaultdict

def calculate_scores():
    rslt = defaultdict(list)
    scores = {"football": [[2, 1], [3, 0]], "cricket": [[120, 30], [95, 5]]}

    for game in scores:
        for match in scores[game]:
            rslt[game].append(sum(match))

    return rslt
```

Dis change yah should sort out di problem an mek di function run smooth an easy, yuh hear?

counterharm_coi:
Mi deh write one Python function fi calculate di total time yuh spend pon di phone each day. But when mi try run di code, it throw a KeyError because di dictionary nuh have all di days listed yet. Yu see, regular dictionary inna Python nuh like when yuh try access key weh nuh deh deh—it just throw error pon yuh face. Di good news a seh weh have defaultdict from di collections module weh can help. Defaultdict automatically put inna empty list fi any day weh yuh mention but nuh set up yet. So yuh code can run smooth an' calculate di time without crash. Here how yuh can set it up:

```python
from collections import defaultdict

def calculate_screen_time():
    screen_time = defaultdict(list)
    daily_usage = {
        "Monday": [30, 45, 20],
        "Tuesday": [60, 15],
        "Friday": [120, 30, 45]
    }

    for day in daily_usage:
        for minutes in daily_usage[day]:
            screen_time[day].append(minutes)

    # Calculate total time per day
    total_time = {day: sum(times) for day, times in screen_time.items()}
    return total_time
```

Now yuh can track yuh screen time proper an' mek sure yuh nuh spend too much time pon di phone. It a good way fi stay balanced an' tek care a yuhself.

original_input:
To connect to a MySQL database using PHP, you can use the following code snippet:

```php
<?php
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "username";
$password = "password";
$dbname = "database_name";

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}
echo "Connected successfully";

// Close connection
$conn->close();
?>
```

